":[{"name":"Eynon","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>Enniaun</i>, an old Welsh personal name ultimately derived from Late Latin <i>Annianus</i>, but also associated with Welsh <i>einion</i> ‘anvil’, taken as implying stability and fortitude. See also   Beynon   and compare   Onion  ."]}]},{"name":"Einion","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: originally a byname meaning ‘anvil’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Fychan","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Welsh: A Welsh name of great antiquity, from vyckan, little, small; i.e. small in stature. Compare the surname Bychan and the Armoric Le Bihan."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Einion Fychan ap Einion was born in 1220, in Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Einion ap Gwalchmai, was 25 and his mother, Gwenllian verch Kenric, was 65. He married Angharad ferch Ednyfed Fychan in 1245, in Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons."},"et":{"1220–":"1220–Surnud","1215–Female":"1215–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1150–1246":"1150–1246","1235–Male":"1235–Surnud","1270–1370":"1270–1370","–1300":"–1300","1195–Male":"1195–Surnud","1156–Female":"1156–Surnud","1220":"1220","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1370":"1370","1150":"1150","1270":"1270","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1246":"1246","1245":"1245","1300":"1300","1156":"1156","about 1235":"umbes 1235","Abt 1270":"umbes 1270","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","Merioneth, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Anglesey, Wales":"Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1220–":"1220–Kuollut","1215–Female":"1215–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1185–Female":"1185–Kuollut","1150–1246":"1150–1246","1235–Male":"1235–Kuollut","1270–1370":"1270–1370","–1300":"–1300","1195–Male":"1195–Kuollut","1156–Female":"1156–Kuollut","1220":"1220","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1370":"1370","1150":"11